WEBVTT

00:00.143 --> 00:30.044
300MB UNiTED TEAM - sunmenghao

00:53.143 --> 00:56.044
<i>Mr. Fire</i>
<i>versus Mr. Ice.</i>

00:57.314 --> 00:58.872
<i>For everything people were</i>
<i>making it out to be</i>

00:58.949 --> 01:01.110
<i>you'd think</i>
<i>it was our first fight.</i>

01:02.419 --> 01:03.784
<i>It wasn't.</i>

01:04.388 --> 01:05.878
<i>And it wouldn't be our last.</i>

01:09.460 --> 01:10.950
<i>And, in local news,</i>

01:11.028 --> 01:14.520
<i>violence between servicemen</i>
<i>and zoot-suiters reached</i>
<i>a new level tonight</i>

01:14.598 --> 01:17.863
<i>after the wives of two sailors</i>
<i>were criminally attacked.</i>

01:17.935 --> 01:20.529
<i>An order listing Los Angeles</i>
<i>as a restricted area</i>

01:20.604 --> 01:21.969
<i>has not deterred the fighting,</i>

01:22.039 --> 01:24.633
<i>but the Los Angeles</i>
<i>Police Department</i>
<i>assures the public</i>

01:24.708 --> 01:27.643
<i>that it has the situation</i>
<i>completely under control.</i>

01:28.712 --> 01:31.681
Hey, sawbuck
on the private chasing
that skinny one over there!

01:31.748 --> 01:33.739
Come on, private!

01:33.817 --> 01:35.546
Come on, private!
That spic's quick!

01:35.619 --> 01:36.916
Jesus Christ!

01:36.987 --> 01:39.683
Double or nothing
on that greaser!
You're on!

01:49.199 --> 01:50.632
Bleichert!

01:52.236 --> 01:53.931
<i>I already knew him</i>
<i>by reputation,</i>

01:54.004 --> 01:55.471
<i>record down pat.</i>

01:56.306 --> 01:59.503
<i>A regular attraction</i>
<i>at the Hollywood</i>
<i>Legion Stadium.</i>

01:59.576 --> 02:01.476
<i>Lee Blanchard.</i>
Bleichert!

02:01.545 --> 02:03.376
<i>43-4-2 as a heavyweight.</i>

02:04.148 --> 02:05.137
Shit!

02:05.215 --> 02:06.512
<i>And he knew me,</i>

02:06.850 --> 02:08.841
<i>Dwight "Bucky" Bleichert.</i>

02:09.520 --> 02:10.748
<i>Light heavy,</i>

02:11.255 --> 02:14.190
<i>36-0-0. Ranked tenth</i>
<i>by</i> Ring Magazine.

02:15.559 --> 02:18.528
<i>Fighting no-name opponents</i>
<i>in a no-man's-land division.</i>

02:25.402 --> 02:26.733
Get out of here!

02:26.803 --> 02:28.498
Hey, get back there.

02:28.572 --> 02:30.699
<i>In our first year</i>
<i>at Central Division Station</i>

02:31.475 --> 02:32.499
<i>we never spoke.</i>

02:32.576 --> 02:34.567
To the Halls of Tripoli,
shitbirds.

02:34.645 --> 02:36.078
Who's this?

02:38.448 --> 02:40.075
Officer Bleichert,

02:41.084 --> 02:43.211
meet <i>Se√±or</i> Tomas Dos Santos.

02:43.353 --> 02:46.618
You came all the way
down here just to roust
some Class B felon?

02:46.690 --> 02:49.887
Came down here, same as you,
to keep from getting killed.

02:49.960 --> 02:52.929
Happened to see some jarheads
beating on a good collar.

02:52.996 --> 02:54.588
I'll take him in the morning.
This is nuts.

02:54.665 --> 02:56.997
We'll never get him
booked tonight.

02:59.303 --> 03:01.066
That's a nice left hook
you got.

03:02.072 --> 03:03.232
Mmm.

03:03.674 --> 03:05.266
Well, you know, old habits.

03:05.876 --> 03:06.968
Yeah.

03:07.544 --> 03:11.036
My girlfriend saw you fight
a couple of times
over at the Olympic.

03:11.114 --> 03:14.015
Said you were good.
Said you were somebody.

03:18.689 --> 03:20.486
Big fish, small pond.

03:21.592 --> 03:23.560
Never made it up to the
big boys' division like you.

03:23.627 --> 03:26.118
My first 20 fights
were stumblebums

03:26.697 --> 03:28.528
handpicked by my manager.

03:28.599 --> 03:30.226
Lucky to survive.

03:31.235 --> 03:33.669
There's a Jew-boy Deputy D.A.
over in Central Warrants,

03:33.737 --> 03:35.170
wets his pants for fighters,

03:35.239 --> 03:37.639
and he promised me
the next spot he can wangle.

03:38.875 --> 03:41.105
<i>Warrants was</i>
<i>local celebrity as a cop.</i>

03:41.178 --> 03:42.975
<i>Warrants was chasing</i>
<i>real criminals</i>

03:43.046 --> 03:45.879
<i>not rousting winos</i>
<i>and wienie waggers in front</i>
<i>of some Midnight Mission.</i>

03:45.949 --> 03:47.439
Hey, Bleichert.
Bleichert.

03:47.517 --> 03:50.145
They want to see you upstairs.
The D.A.'s office.

03:50.220 --> 03:52.586
<i>Jew-boy D.A.s</i>
<i>with hard-ons for fighters.</i>

03:52.656 --> 03:54.783
<i>Transfers, promotions...</i>
Officer Bleichert.

03:54.858 --> 03:56.325
<i>Back then,</i>
<i>I told myself I didn't care.</i>

03:56.393 --> 03:57.951
Gentlemen, Bucky Bleichert.

03:58.028 --> 03:59.757
Bucky,
this is Chief Ted Green.

03:59.830 --> 04:00.819
Nice to meet you.

04:00.897 --> 04:03.263
Deputy District Attorney
Ellis Loew.

04:04.768 --> 04:06.201
Read that out loud, Dwight.

04:06.270 --> 04:08.170
That's running
in the <i>Sunday Times</i>.

04:09.273 --> 04:10.638
"Before the war,
the City of Angels

04:10.707 --> 04:13.107
"was graced
with two local fighters,

04:13.176 --> 04:16.441
"pugilists with styles
as different as fire and ice.

04:16.513 --> 04:18.845
"Lee Blanchard..."

04:19.650 --> 04:20.981
Excuse me.

04:21.251 --> 04:23.310
"Mr. Fire and Mr. Ice
never fought each other

04:23.387 --> 04:25.981
"but duty brought them
to the Los Angeles
Police Department.

04:26.056 --> 04:29.548
"Blanchard cracked
the Boulevard-Citizens
Bank robbery case in 1939

04:29.626 --> 04:32.561
"and captured thrill-killer,
Tomas Dos Santos.

04:32.629 --> 04:35.359
"Bleichert
served with distinction
during the Zoot Suit Wars."

04:35.432 --> 04:37.229
Jump to the end.
Right, boss.

04:37.301 --> 04:40.566
"On Election Day, voters are
going to be asked to vote
on a bond proposal

04:40.637 --> 04:42.264
"to upgrade
the LAPD's equipment

04:42.339 --> 04:45.206
"and provide for an 8%
pay raise for all personnel.

04:45.275 --> 04:48.335
"Keep in mind the examples
of Mr. Fire and Mr. Ice.

04:48.412 --> 04:50.607
"Vote 'Yes' on Proposition B."

04:50.781 --> 04:51.975
What do you think?

04:52.649 --> 04:53.673
Subtle.

04:53.750 --> 04:54.774
Prop B's a loser right now,

04:54.851 --> 04:56.216
but I think if we can
drum up some publicity

04:56.286 --> 04:58.846
we can get it passed
in next month's election.

04:58.922 --> 05:00.150
Yes, sir.
Fire and Ice.

05:00.223 --> 05:02.691
Ten rounds, Academy Gym,
three weeks from now,
before the election,

05:02.759 --> 05:03.919
all gate to charity.

05:03.994 --> 05:06.485
After that, we bring back
the boxing team.

05:06.563 --> 05:08.463
What do you say, Bucky?
You in?

05:08.532 --> 05:10.124
I got to
get back in shape.

05:10.200 --> 05:11.258
Bucky.

05:11.335 --> 05:12.529
Lee.

05:12.602 --> 05:14.229
I'd like you to meet Kay Lake.

05:14.304 --> 05:16.204
Hello.
Hello.

05:16.273 --> 05:17.501
You beefing up?

05:17.574 --> 05:18.836
You know.

05:18.909 --> 05:21.309
I was just telling Kay here
about our new hobby.

05:21.378 --> 05:22.606
Are you a fight fan,
Miss Lake?

05:22.679 --> 05:24.237
No, Lee used to drag me.

05:24.314 --> 05:26.680
I was taking art classes,
so I'd sketch.

05:26.750 --> 05:28.081
She made me quit fighting
the smokers.

05:28.151 --> 05:29.709
Didn't want me doing
the "Vegetable Shuffle."

05:29.786 --> 05:31.617
I promise not to hurt you.

05:31.688 --> 05:33.280
That won't make Loew
very happy.

05:33.357 --> 05:34.847
Oh, he's got money on me?

05:34.925 --> 05:37.723
Seems that way.
You win, you get Warrants.

05:38.061 --> 05:39.358
What's in it for you?

05:39.429 --> 05:41.590
Well, betting works both ways.

05:41.665 --> 05:43.064
My girl's got a taste
for nice things

05:43.133 --> 05:45.533
and I can't afford to
let her down.

05:45.602 --> 05:46.728
Right, babe?

05:46.803 --> 05:48.828
Keep talking about me
in third person.

05:48.905 --> 05:50.304
It sends me.

05:50.607 --> 05:52.268
What do you think of all this,
Miss Lake?

05:52.342 --> 05:56.676
Well, for civic reasons,
I hope the LAPD is ridiculed
for perpetrating this farce.

05:56.747 --> 05:59.181
For personal reasons,
I hope Lee wins.

05:59.249 --> 06:02.116
And, for esthetic reasons,
I hope you both look good
with your shirts off.

06:21.405 --> 06:22.497
Papa?

06:38.321 --> 06:40.016
<i>Guten Tag</i>, Dwight.

06:40.090 --> 06:41.114
English, Papa.

06:52.669 --> 06:55.467
Hey, you haven't finished
this plane yet.

06:56.206 --> 06:57.969
Can you finish that?

07:00.143 --> 07:01.667
Here, sit down.

07:09.920 --> 07:11.615
If you could just come by
and clean the place up,

07:11.688 --> 07:13.883
keep an eye on him
for a week or so.

07:16.693 --> 07:18.160
I know I still owe you.

07:21.965 --> 07:24.058
Guess what I hear is right.

07:24.868 --> 07:26.460
You'll want to place this
with Mickey Cohen's indie.

07:26.536 --> 07:28.265
He's got Blanchard, 2-1.

07:30.040 --> 07:31.803
That confident, huh?

07:32.876 --> 07:34.776
You done your homework?

07:36.179 --> 07:38.306
Yeah. I've done my homework.

07:43.787 --> 07:45.914
I'm not betting on me, Pete.

07:48.024 --> 07:50.049
Blanchard's the hero here.

07:50.527 --> 07:51.994
That's the way
the story's supposed to go.

07:52.062 --> 07:53.427
I'm just the other guy.

08:02.739 --> 08:05.105
Well, at least he looks good
with his shirt off.

08:09.212 --> 08:11.112
Where's your sketchpad?

08:11.314 --> 08:12.679
I was never any good.

08:12.749 --> 08:15.081
Ended up with a Master's
in History.

08:16.152 --> 08:17.915
Education's
an expensive habit.

08:18.989 --> 08:20.581
Lee paid for it.

08:21.191 --> 08:22.658
He shouldn't have
quit fighting.

08:22.726 --> 08:24.284
I asked him to.

08:24.361 --> 08:27.455
Besides, police work
gives him a sense of order.

08:30.233 --> 08:32.633
Do you have a girlfriend,
Dwight?

08:33.169 --> 08:35.694
I'm saving myself
for Rita Hayworth.

08:41.077 --> 08:43.341
So he quits
fighting for you,
puts you through school.

08:43.413 --> 08:45.745
Quite a guy. Quite a pair.

08:45.949 --> 08:47.849
Why aren't you married?

08:51.154 --> 08:53.315
You know,
shacking's against regs.
Probably cost him a stripe.

08:53.390 --> 08:56.188
So where's the diamonds
and the bassinets, huh?

08:58.128 --> 09:00.688
Well, you'd have
to sleep together
for that, Dwight.

09:13.243 --> 09:15.643
<i>The gym was packed</i>
<i>to the rafters.</i>

09:16.513 --> 09:19.346
<i>A wild crowd hungry</i>
<i>to see what was in us.</i>

09:21.151 --> 09:23.244
<i>I already knew what was in us.</i>

09:23.320 --> 09:25.288
<i>Ambition, pride,</i>

09:25.922 --> 09:28.914
<i>dissatisfaction at a life</i>
<i>turned just the wrong way.</i>

09:28.992 --> 09:30.459
Luck, Dwight.

09:32.028 --> 09:33.791
Come on.

09:45.108 --> 09:46.632
Keep it clean!

10:13.670 --> 10:17.071
<i>I feel it's my duty</i>
<i>as a friend to tell you this,</i>

10:17.674 --> 10:19.574
<i>make it look good.</i>

10:33.023 --> 10:34.251
One!

10:35.025 --> 10:36.083
Two!

10:36.793 --> 10:37.953
Three!

10:38.695 --> 10:39.855
Four!

10:40.597 --> 10:41.689
Five!

10:44.200 --> 10:45.258
Six!

10:45.435 --> 10:47.096
<i>I lost a lot of things</i>
<i>in life...</i>

10:47.170 --> 10:48.501
Seven!

10:49.839 --> 10:51.397
<i>...but never</i>
<i>a fight for money.</i>

10:51.474 --> 10:52.668
Eight!

11:08.858 --> 11:12.385
<i>I was trading Warrants</i>
<i>for a close-out on old</i>
<i>bad debts.</i>

11:13.029 --> 11:14.394
<i>The eight grand</i>
<i>I was going to clear</i>

11:14.464 --> 11:15.692
<i>was enough</i>
<i>to maintain the old man</i>

11:15.765 --> 11:18.666
<i>in a good, clean rest home</i>
<i>for three years.</i>

11:18.902 --> 11:20.164
<i>The late-round tank job,</i>

11:20.236 --> 11:22.363
<i>enough to convince myself</i>
<i>I wasn't a complete coward.</i>

11:23.506 --> 11:24.564
Box!

11:30.146 --> 11:31.773
Finish the fight!

11:32.282 --> 11:33.943
Where's that hook?

12:25.001 --> 12:26.366
You're out!

12:44.654 --> 12:46.246
Give me a smile.

12:57.867 --> 12:59.892
It's nice, isn't it, Papa?

13:00.503 --> 13:02.164
What do you think?

13:21.958 --> 13:23.653
Hey! Canvasback!

13:30.867 --> 13:32.232
Canvasback!

13:38.842 --> 13:41.572
You going to hide in there
another week?

13:41.778 --> 13:43.541
Ain't you bored yet?

13:44.180 --> 13:45.670
Nice chompers.

13:46.149 --> 13:47.844
So, you want to work Warrants?

13:47.917 --> 13:49.578
I lost.
What about Loew's deal?

13:49.652 --> 13:53.019
Don't you read the papers?
The bond passed yesterday.

13:53.857 --> 13:55.085
You want the job?

13:56.826 --> 13:58.555
Atta boy, Mr. Ice.

13:59.996 --> 14:01.156
Champ!

14:02.098 --> 14:03.759
Show them what's
under the lip, boss.

14:03.833 --> 14:05.425
Right over here.

14:05.969 --> 14:09.268
Officer Bleichert,
the men of Central Dicks.

14:09.706 --> 14:13.733
Homicide,
Ad Vice, Bunco, et cetera.
I'm Captain John Tierney.

14:14.611 --> 14:16.135
You and Lee
are the white men of the hour,

14:16.212 --> 14:18.112
so I hope
you enjoyed your ovation.

14:18.181 --> 14:20.206
You won't get another one
till you retire.

14:21.851 --> 14:24.012
Enough horse shit!
Listen!

14:24.520 --> 14:26.112
This is the felony
summary report

14:26.189 --> 14:29.249
for the week ending
November 14, 1946.

14:29.325 --> 14:31.657
First, two liquor store
stickups

14:31.895 --> 14:35.194
Broadway and Seventh,
and Hill Liquor in Chinatown.

14:35.465 --> 14:37.126
That one comes
with a pistol whipping,

14:37.267 --> 14:39.132
my personal favorite.

14:39.202 --> 14:40.794
Russ Millard, Homicides.

14:40.870 --> 14:42.565
Hi.
How are you?

14:42.639 --> 14:44.539
My wife and kids thank you
for the raise, Officer.

14:44.607 --> 14:47.337
Officer Bleichert,
I'm Bill Koenig.
This is Fritz Vogel.

14:47.410 --> 14:49.640
Welcome aboard.
Pleasure to meet you.

14:51.180 --> 14:53.978
Lee, I heard something
you ought to know.

14:54.050 --> 14:57.884
I was over at County Parole,
and Bobby DeWitt got
an "A" number.

14:57.954 --> 15:00.184
He'll be released to L.A.
in late January.

15:00.256 --> 15:01.723
Thanks, Russ.

15:05.328 --> 15:06.659
Who's Bobby DeWitt?

15:06.729 --> 15:07.991
Old beef.

15:08.431 --> 15:10.092
Pot roast tonight?

15:22.745 --> 15:24.440
Don't say anything
about DeWitt.

15:24.514 --> 15:25.845
It'll upset Kay.

15:26.549 --> 15:27.641
Sure.

15:35.458 --> 15:36.823
Nice place.

15:36.893 --> 15:38.292
Fight stash.

15:39.595 --> 15:40.755
Hello.

15:40.830 --> 15:43.128
Dwight.
Glad you could make it.

15:44.968 --> 15:46.936
How was your first day?

15:47.971 --> 15:51.338
Mostly backslaps and paperwork
if I know those boys.

15:54.077 --> 15:56.170
And look at that smile now.

16:06.956 --> 16:09.151
Well, this is nice,
isn't it?

16:10.393 --> 16:11.451
What?

16:11.527 --> 16:13.222
You and Lee partners.
It's nice.

16:13.296 --> 16:16.424
It couldn't have worked out
better if you'd planned it,
could it, Dwight?

16:16.499 --> 16:17.761
Well, I could've beat him.

16:17.834 --> 16:19.301
Except you didn't.

16:19.369 --> 16:22.896
I don't know, sweetheart.
Bucky was somebody
back in the day.

16:22.972 --> 16:24.098
And here we all are...

16:24.173 --> 16:25.504
It's nice.

16:25.742 --> 16:26.936
It's more than nice.

16:27.010 --> 16:30.468
Might even be worth those
front teeth of yours, Dwight.

16:31.247 --> 16:32.441
A toast

16:33.416 --> 16:34.474
to Proposition B.

16:34.550 --> 16:36.211
To the Bleichert-Blanchard
rematch,

16:36.285 --> 16:37.843
bigger than
Louis-Schmeling.

16:37.920 --> 16:40.218
To my supercops!

16:40.590 --> 16:41.682
To us!

16:45.395 --> 16:46.760
<i>From November</i>
<i>through the New Year,</i>

16:46.829 --> 16:49.354
<i>Lee and I captured</i>
<i>11 hard felons,</i>

16:49.432 --> 16:53.391
<i>18 traffic warrantees</i>
<i>and three parole</i>
<i>and probation absconders.</i>

16:55.371 --> 16:59.432
<i>After tours of duty,</i>
<i>Lee and I would go</i>
<i>to the house and find Kay.</i>

17:00.143 --> 17:01.974
<i>Sometimes she'd make</i>
<i>dinner for us.</i>

17:02.045 --> 17:05.572
<i>Other times, the three of us</i>
<i>would go out on the town.</i>

17:26.869 --> 17:28.666
<i>Always she'd be there</i>

17:28.871 --> 17:31.567
<i>never between us,</i>
<i>always in the middle.</i>

18:27.363 --> 18:28.796
<i>For New Year's,</i>
<i>we headed downtown</i>

18:28.865 --> 18:31.095
<i>to a dinner club</i>
<i>owned by Morrie Friedman,</i>

18:31.501 --> 18:32.900
<i>a friend of Mickey Cohen's</i>

18:33.169 --> 18:35.364
<i>who sometimes clued</i>
<i>Lee in to L.A. drug traffic.</i>

18:35.438 --> 18:38.032
Happy New Year!

18:59.562 --> 19:01.894
<i>It was the best time</i>
<i>of my life.</i>

19:28.491 --> 19:31.358
Listen up!
Gentlemen, thank you.

19:31.561 --> 19:32.994
"Raymond 'Junior' Nash.

19:33.062 --> 19:36.998
"Statutory rape,
armed robbery, felony mayhem.

19:37.600 --> 19:40.569
"Texas State Prison.
Alcatraz."

19:40.903 --> 19:42.700
Mr. Nash pistol-whipped
a little old lady

19:42.772 --> 19:44.865
at a stickup near
Leimert Park,
Tuesday morning.

19:44.941 --> 19:46.169
She died last night.

19:46.242 --> 19:47.800
Anything common
in the sex beefs?

19:47.877 --> 19:49.742
Negro girls. Young ones.

19:50.246 --> 19:52.646
All the complainants
have been coloreds.

19:52.848 --> 19:55.043
<i>Junior Nash</i>
<i>was an inbred Okie shit-kicker</i>

19:55.117 --> 19:57.585
<i>who came west and took</i>
<i>all us locals for easy marks</i>

19:57.653 --> 20:00.747
<i>just because</i>
<i>we prefer our cowboys</i>
<i>to look like Gene Autry.</i>

20:00.823 --> 20:02.450
<i>Of course, I didn't care</i>
<i>if he was a hard man</i>

20:02.525 --> 20:04.254
<i>or what he thought</i>
<i>about anything.</i>

20:04.327 --> 20:07.296
<i>He raped children and beat</i>
<i>senior citizens to death.</i>

20:07.430 --> 20:10.365
<i>He was a coward</i>
<i>and I wanted to put him down.</i>

20:10.600 --> 20:15.264
I got a tip for the hophead
who's going to be at Norton
and Coliseum tonight.

20:16.005 --> 20:17.165
Hey, partner,
everything good to go?

20:17.240 --> 20:18.264
Yeah.

20:18.341 --> 20:21.572
Nash just got a fuck pad
on Norton and Coliseum.

20:56.712 --> 20:58.373
Scram! Get out of here!

20:58.447 --> 20:59.675
Okay!

20:59.749 --> 21:00.841
Fine.

21:02.685 --> 21:04.812
Don't make me say it twice!
All right! We're going!

21:04.887 --> 21:06.377
Make some money, man.

21:25.574 --> 21:29.476
Oh, my! Oh, help!
Help me! Help, somebody!

21:29.545 --> 21:32.639
Please! Help!
Stop! Stop the car!

21:32.715 --> 21:36.310
Please stop! Stop! Stop!

21:50.399 --> 21:52.731
Listen. I'm broke.

21:53.769 --> 21:55.760
Baby,
he's gonna cut us
a real good deal on this.

21:55.838 --> 21:57.669
I have been knowing him
for a long time.

21:57.740 --> 21:59.674
You ain't got to worry
about a thing, okay?

21:59.742 --> 22:02.210
You ain't got to worry.
I got this dirty cop.

22:02.278 --> 22:03.472
Mmm-hmm.

22:03.846 --> 22:05.609
He's going to
take care of me real soon.

22:05.681 --> 22:06.705
And I mean real soon.

22:06.782 --> 22:08.147
Dirty cop?

22:09.051 --> 22:11.679
I haven't heard
of a clean cop, Baxter.

22:11.754 --> 22:13.722
I just want to go home.
Why do you do this to me, huh?

22:13.789 --> 22:15.654
Why? Why this? Why? Why?

22:15.725 --> 22:18.455
Same reason
why you do this to me.
You know why I do this to you.

22:18.527 --> 22:20.825
Where is this guy?
He's right there.
We almost there. Come on.

22:20.896 --> 22:22.454
Come on, baby! Come on.

22:22.531 --> 22:23.896
Oh, God,
I got to follow you now?

22:23.966 --> 22:25.433
Come on.

22:26.602 --> 22:28.900
Listen, this is the last time.

22:29.105 --> 22:30.629
Bucky, wake up.

22:38.514 --> 22:40.846
Bucky, look out! Get down!

22:41.584 --> 22:45.213
<i>I was half-asleep,</i>
<i>but Lee had his boxer's wits</i>
<i>about him.</i>

22:46.222 --> 22:48.213
<i>He felt the blow coming.</i>

22:49.558 --> 22:51.219
<i>He saved my life.</i>

23:16.051 --> 23:18.281
Get your motherfucking
hands off me, man.
I ain't done nothing!

23:18.354 --> 23:20.481
Yeah, what do you call that
shooting gallery back there?

23:24.894 --> 23:26.225
Fuck you, man!

23:53.689 --> 23:54.747
Lee!

23:58.060 --> 23:59.118
Lee!

24:05.468 --> 24:07.333
Well, that's about it.

24:08.070 --> 24:12.063
Thank you
for your time, Detective,
and for the good police work.

24:12.608 --> 24:14.667
Blanchard knew the white guy,
I guess.

24:14.743 --> 24:16.176
Busted him once.

24:16.645 --> 24:18.636
He snitched for Lee
a couple of times.

24:19.648 --> 24:21.115
Baxter Fitch.

24:22.117 --> 24:24.244
It's a busy neighborhood.

24:24.320 --> 24:26.413
Take a look at top billing.

24:44.974 --> 24:47.738
All right, easy.
Guys, guys. Please.

24:49.111 --> 24:52.012
Don't trample over everything,
please. Easy.

24:52.715 --> 24:54.205
Secure the area.

24:54.283 --> 24:57.411
All right, listen up.
No reporters view the body.

24:57.486 --> 24:59.545
You photo men, finish
taking your pictures now.

24:59.622 --> 25:02.682
Coroner's men,
put a sheet on the body
as soon as they are done.

25:02.758 --> 25:04.692
We set up a perimeter
six feet back.

25:04.760 --> 25:07.320
Any reporter crosses it,
arrest him.

25:07.396 --> 25:09.956
Now, gentlemen, before
this gets out of hand,

25:10.032 --> 25:12.091
let's put the kibosh
on something.

25:12.868 --> 25:14.927
With publicity,
you get confessions.

25:15.004 --> 25:17.802
With confessions,
you get crazies,
liars and false leads.

25:17.873 --> 25:20.273
So, we keep some things quiet.

25:20.576 --> 25:23.875
The ear-to-ear
facial lacerations,

25:24.213 --> 25:25.703
disembowelment,

25:25.781 --> 25:28.443
you keep this information
to yourselves.

25:28.517 --> 25:30.883
Not your wives,
not your girlfriends,

25:30.953 --> 25:33.513
no other officers,
and I mean no...

25:34.023 --> 25:35.957
Bleichert, what the hell
are you doing here?

25:36.025 --> 25:37.185
Where the hell's Blanchard?

25:37.259 --> 25:38.624
He's right here.

25:39.361 --> 25:41.795
Nash might be renting a room
in that building over there.

25:41.864 --> 25:43.661
I heard something
on the radio about
a shooting.

25:43.732 --> 25:44.960
Was that Nash?
No.

25:46.569 --> 25:48.059
We had some trouble.

25:52.274 --> 25:54.242
Stand back!
Get back of the line!

25:54.310 --> 25:55.971
Move back. Come on, boys.

25:56.045 --> 25:57.535
Get them back!

25:59.915 --> 26:02.042
Hey, Raymond Nash, remember?

26:02.685 --> 26:04.277
We need to go
check out that room.

26:04.353 --> 26:05.650
Nash didn't do this.

26:06.221 --> 26:08.951
No. But he beat
a woman to death.

26:09.024 --> 26:10.753
That's why
he's our priority warrantee.

26:14.730 --> 26:18.826
All right!
I need everybody right now!

26:20.536 --> 26:21.594
Baby.

26:27.009 --> 26:28.135
What happened?

26:28.210 --> 26:29.541
Nothing.
I don't want to talk about it.

26:29.612 --> 26:34.015
Lee, Baxter Fitch just
happened to be there?
What happened, Lee?

26:38.354 --> 26:39.446
What do you know about it?

26:39.521 --> 26:42.081
I know you, Lee.
I know you, Lee.

26:45.761 --> 26:46.819
Lee...

26:46.895 --> 26:49.125
He knew one of the guys, so...

26:52.768 --> 26:54.861
Dwight, was it you or them?

26:58.874 --> 27:00.501
He saved my life.

27:05.481 --> 27:07.676
Hey, Kay,
who's Bobby DeWitt?

27:09.585 --> 27:11.348
I know he's an old beef
of Lee's.

27:12.788 --> 27:15.757
But he doesn't
want to talk about it
and he gets out in a week.

27:18.027 --> 27:19.756
You know who he is?

27:30.806 --> 27:32.535
I'm scared, Dwight.

27:35.911 --> 27:37.708
I'll take care of it.

27:40.215 --> 27:42.012
You don't know Bobby.

28:33.669 --> 28:35.136
<i>Bobby DeWitt.</i>

28:36.271 --> 28:38.865
<i>Who are these men</i>
<i>who feed on others?</i>

28:39.842 --> 28:44.108
<i>What do they feel</i>
<i>when they cut their names</i>
<i>into somebody else's life?</i>

28:51.019 --> 28:53.681
<i>It was the case</i>
<i>that made Lee's career.</i>

28:53.756 --> 28:57.055
<i>He'd never said a word</i>
<i>about it and I'd never asked.</i>

28:57.126 --> 28:59.959
<i>One of Lee's snitches</i>
<i>fingered Bobby DeWitt,</i>

29:00.162 --> 29:03.893
<i>a small-time pimp</i>
<i>with a yard-long rap,</i>
<i>as the brains behind the job.</i>

29:03.966 --> 29:07.129
<i>DeWitt never</i>
<i>spoke the entire trial,</i>
<i>never coughing up the dough</i>

29:07.202 --> 29:10.467
<i>even after damning</i>
<i>character testimony</i>
<i>from some of his girls</i>

29:10.539 --> 29:12.302
<i>including one Katherine Lake,</i>

29:13.208 --> 29:14.835
<i>formerly of Sioux Falls,</i>
<i>South Dakota,</i>

29:14.910 --> 29:16.673
<i>and looking to go straight.</i>

29:17.713 --> 29:20.307
<i>DeWitt got 10 to life</i>
<i>in San Quentin.</i>

29:20.415 --> 29:21.780
<i>Lee got Kay</i>

29:22.851 --> 29:25.445
<i>or maybe it was</i>
<i>the other way around.</i>

29:31.794 --> 29:34.422
We're supposed to be
looking for Nash.

29:34.496 --> 29:35.758
Priority.

29:36.298 --> 29:38.357
Yeah, priority
for Homicide Division, not us.

29:38.433 --> 29:40.628
Nice white girl gets snuffed.

29:40.936 --> 29:43.598
Got to show the voters
they did the right thing
passing the bond issue.

29:43.672 --> 29:46.300
It's A-plus, Buck.
We don't miss this.

29:47.910 --> 29:50.344
Maybe she wasn't
such a nice girl.

29:50.612 --> 29:54.742
Maybe that old lady
that Nash snuffed was
somebody's loving granny.

29:56.785 --> 29:58.184
Maybe we let
the Bureau handle this

29:58.253 --> 30:01.984
and we get back to our job
before Nash snuffs
somebody else.

30:04.226 --> 30:06.023
Got any other maybes?

30:07.062 --> 30:09.758
Yeah, maybe we've had
enough headlines.

30:10.332 --> 30:12.357
With or without you, Buck.

30:15.037 --> 30:16.129
With or without you.

30:16.805 --> 30:19.603
Therefore, we have created
a special unit

30:19.808 --> 30:22.072
which will include a number
of highly trained officers

30:22.144 --> 30:24.135
including
Detective Russell Millard,

30:24.213 --> 30:26.272
our very own Mr. Fire

30:26.515 --> 30:28.506
and his partner, Mr. Ice.

30:28.617 --> 30:31.586
Mr. Loew, can you assure
the public that you will find

30:31.653 --> 30:33.416
the murderer
before he strikes again?

30:33.488 --> 30:35.080
I can guarantee you

30:35.157 --> 30:38.217
this killer will be caught.

30:39.494 --> 30:41.587
You got us detached?
Slow and easy, Buck.

30:41.663 --> 30:45.030
I gave Loew a memo saying
Nash blew our jurisdiction.

30:45.434 --> 30:46.901
You did what?

30:47.469 --> 30:49.130
Are you fucking nuts?
It's all right.

30:49.204 --> 30:51.297
The APB still stands.
He's covered.

30:51.373 --> 30:52.499
This is the main event.

30:52.574 --> 30:55.236
Nash is pure undercard.
Just give me another week
with this girl.

30:55.310 --> 30:57.505
What's your problem
with this?

30:57.579 --> 30:59.240
Letting Nash slip.

31:04.286 --> 31:08.848
On gross pathology,
we have a female Caucasian
between 16 and 30.

31:08.924 --> 31:11.222
The cadaver
is presented in two halves

31:11.293 --> 31:13.955
with bisection
level with the umbilicus.

31:14.897 --> 31:18.094
Through and through
lacerations
of both mouth corners.

31:18.166 --> 31:21.158
No visible bruising
on the neck.

31:21.670 --> 31:25.629
Rectangular abrasions
on the wing tips
of the sphenoid bones.

31:26.541 --> 31:29.977
And, oh!
A puncture wound, here,

31:31.079 --> 31:33.946
in the palm.
On the palm of the right hand.

31:34.583 --> 31:35.743
There.

31:36.151 --> 31:41.054
Investigation of upper half
abdominal cavity reveals
no free-flowing blood.

31:41.723 --> 31:45.716
Intestines, stomach,
spleen, liver, all removed.

31:47.296 --> 31:48.957
Is it all right to smoke,
Doctor?

31:49.031 --> 31:50.498
She won't mind.

31:50.565 --> 31:55.161
Lower half of cadaver
reveals removal
of all reproductive organs.

31:55.370 --> 31:57.099
Both legs broken at the knee.

31:57.172 --> 31:58.503
Questions.

31:58.740 --> 32:01.174
What's your best guess?
Well, here's what she wasn't,

32:01.243 --> 32:03.040
she wasn't raped
and she wasn't pregnant.

32:03.111 --> 32:04.544
In terms of the nitty-gritty,

32:04.613 --> 32:08.014
the cause of death
is either the mouth wound here

32:08.283 --> 32:11.548
or she was beaten to death
with something like
a baseball bat.

32:11.620 --> 32:12.882
What about her insides?

32:12.955 --> 32:15.014
They came out posthumously.

32:15.090 --> 32:17.991
I say then he drained
the blood from the body

32:18.060 --> 32:20.528
and washed it clean,
probably in a bathtub.

32:20.595 --> 32:22.563
Have you got a name yet?

32:22.965 --> 32:24.762
"Elizabeth Ann Short.

32:26.001 --> 32:28.902
"Date of birth,
July 29, 1924,

32:28.971 --> 32:30.336
"Medford, Massachusetts."

32:30.839 --> 32:33.205
Cops popped her in '43.
Santa Barbara.

32:33.275 --> 32:34.799
Underage drinking.

32:34.876 --> 32:37.071
Other than that, she's clean.

32:37.145 --> 32:39.875
Four sisters,
parents divorced,
her father's here in L.A.

32:39.948 --> 32:43.213
Oh, and I hear he sold
some old photos of her
to the <i>Herald</i>.

32:43.552 --> 32:46.817
I got an alibi just in case
you think I did it.

32:47.022 --> 32:50.116
Tighter than a crab's ass,
and that is airtight.

32:51.426 --> 32:52.984
Detective Bleichert,
Mr. Short.

32:53.061 --> 32:54.392
This is Detective Blanchard.

32:54.463 --> 32:57.125
We would like to
express our condolences
for the loss of your daughter.

32:57.199 --> 32:59.190
Yeah, I know who you are.

32:59.634 --> 33:02.728
Neither of you'd have lasted
a round against Jim Jeffries.

33:02.804 --> 33:05.637
And as for Betty,
she called the tune,
she paid the piper.

33:05.707 --> 33:06.901
You want to hear my alibi?

33:06.975 --> 33:08.806
Yeah, since you're
so anxious to tell it.

33:08.877 --> 33:11.107
Johnny on the spot
here at the diner.

33:11.179 --> 33:13.647
Twenty-seven straight hours
at that grill.

33:13.715 --> 33:16.013
Twenty-seven straight,
last 17 overtime.

33:16.084 --> 33:17.346
You ask anybody here.

33:17.419 --> 33:19.751
They'll alibi me up
tighter than a popcorn fart

33:19.821 --> 33:20.845
and that's
pretty fucking tight.

33:20.922 --> 33:23.220
When was the last time
you saw your daughter,
Mr. Short?

33:23.291 --> 33:26.089
Betty came west in '43,
stars in her eyes.

33:26.762 --> 33:29.595
I promised her three squares
and a five-spot,
she kept the house tidy.

33:29.664 --> 33:30.824
She live with you then?

33:30.899 --> 33:32.696
I gave her the boot in July.

33:33.168 --> 33:36.433
Moved to Santa Barbara.
Sent me a postcard
a couple weeks later.

33:36.505 --> 33:38.132
Some soldier
beat her up pretty bad.

33:38.206 --> 33:39.867
That's the last
I heard from her.

33:39.941 --> 33:41.533
I need three pigs
in a blanket.

33:41.610 --> 33:43.976
Keep your fucking panties on.

33:44.046 --> 33:46.139
Was that soldier
her boyfriend, Mr. Short?

33:46.214 --> 33:48.842
Boyfriend?
They were all her boyfriends.

33:49.251 --> 33:51.549
As long as they wore
a uniform.

33:51.953 --> 33:54.478
See, Betty believed in
quantity before quality.

33:54.556 --> 33:55.955
You calling your
own daughter a tramp?

33:56.024 --> 33:57.685
I got five daughters.

33:57.759 --> 33:59.852
One rotten apple ain't so bad.

33:59.928 --> 34:02.726
Well, maybe this time
she had a boyfriend.

34:02.831 --> 34:03.991
Maybe.

34:04.132 --> 34:05.360
Any names, Mr. Short?

34:05.434 --> 34:08.164
Look, Tom, Dick, Harry,
it don't matter.

34:12.441 --> 34:15.171
She said she was looking
for movie work,

34:16.678 --> 34:18.339
but she just paraded
Hollywood Boulevard

34:18.413 --> 34:20.210
in those black get-ups
of hers.

34:21.450 --> 34:24.544
I mean, who wouldn't get
herself killed doing that,
huh?

34:25.220 --> 34:26.687
Who wouldn't?

34:32.928 --> 34:36.659
We just got handed the entire
U.S. armed forces as suspects.

34:37.466 --> 34:39.161
Flip to see
who writes it up?

34:39.234 --> 34:41.395
I'm staking
Nash's pad tonight.

34:41.470 --> 34:44.997
See if we get any strange
drive-bys at the murder scene.

34:45.273 --> 34:48.242
Do me a favor. Stop by
and check on Kay, will you?

34:48.310 --> 34:49.675
Yeah, sure.

34:53.181 --> 34:54.671
Hello, Dwight.

34:56.985 --> 34:58.919
How'd you know it was me?

34:58.987 --> 35:00.352
Lee stomps.

35:02.457 --> 35:04.220
Is Lee working late?
Mmm.

35:05.694 --> 35:07.161
What's wrong?

35:09.598 --> 35:11.793
He's all bent out of shape
on this dead girl.

35:14.269 --> 35:16.134
He's going
a little squirrelly.

35:16.204 --> 35:17.967
Benzedrine, I think.

35:22.310 --> 35:24.278
Did you read the papers?

35:24.379 --> 35:28.338
She's being played up
as the hottest number
since the atom bomb.

35:28.717 --> 35:32.551
Ellis Loew's looking
to make a career on it.
I think Lee's not far behind.

35:32.621 --> 35:34.145
What about you?

35:35.090 --> 35:36.580
What about me?

35:37.993 --> 35:40.587
What's going to happen to us,
Dwight?

35:46.334 --> 35:48.700
The three of us, I don't know.
No, us.

35:49.237 --> 35:50.966
Just the two of us.

36:02.984 --> 36:04.008
Us.

36:09.658 --> 36:10.682
Kay,

36:16.231 --> 36:18.199
there is no two of us.

36:22.170 --> 36:23.762
He's my partner.

36:27.375 --> 36:29.240
And that's everything.

36:29.544 --> 36:31.444
He's done a lot for me.

36:33.515 --> 36:35.608
He's done even more for me.

36:44.593 --> 36:46.686
There's food in the fridge.

36:47.062 --> 36:48.427
Good night.

37:27.068 --> 37:29.969
Thank our friend Bevo Means
at the <i>Examiner</i>.

37:30.171 --> 37:33.299
See, Bevo's painting
Betty in a black dress
like some actress

37:33.375 --> 37:36.435
in that Alan Ladd movie,
<i>Blue Dahlia.</i>

37:36.544 --> 37:38.011
Should triple our confessions.

37:38.079 --> 37:39.103
Great.

37:39.180 --> 37:41.239
Hollywood will fuck you
when no one else will.

37:41.316 --> 37:43.511
Hey, Johnson,
go get a smoke.

37:46.755 --> 37:48.620
What do you want to do?
I want to go back to Warrants.

37:48.690 --> 37:49.679
No dice.

37:49.758 --> 37:52.352
You're a bright penny,
Bleichert,
and I need you here.

37:54.029 --> 37:56.964
These are Betty's last known
residences and associates.

37:57.032 --> 37:59.660
You go to University Station,
pick up Bill Koenig.
Fritzie's sick.

37:59.734 --> 38:00.996
Lieutenant...

38:01.069 --> 38:02.366
No. You call me Russ

38:02.637 --> 38:03.934
and you get out of here.

38:08.610 --> 38:10.305
So, how do you want
to play this, Sarge?

38:10.378 --> 38:12.676
Fritzie usually does
the talking.

38:12.747 --> 38:14.112
Muscle job?

38:15.250 --> 38:18.048
Why don't you let me
try and talk to her?

38:25.226 --> 38:27.251
All right, first question,

38:29.998 --> 38:32.193
does a Lorna Mertz
live here?

38:32.801 --> 38:34.200
She used to.

38:34.836 --> 38:36.667
She skipped town this morning.

38:36.738 --> 38:40.265
But I'm holding this suitcase
till she ponies up
the back rent.

38:40.342 --> 38:41.707
Is this it?

38:50.218 --> 38:52.311
Miss Short moved around
quite a bit, too, didn't she?

38:52.387 --> 38:53.479
Was anybody threatening her?

38:53.555 --> 38:54.715
Poor Betty.

38:54.789 --> 38:56.450
Her problem wasn't
too many enemies.

38:56.524 --> 38:58.014
It was too many friends.

38:58.660 --> 39:00.252
I gathered that.

39:01.029 --> 39:02.496
Okay,
let's change the subject.

39:02.564 --> 39:03.656
All right.

39:03.732 --> 39:06.132
How about the world
of high finance?

39:06.201 --> 39:07.395
How about the movies?

39:07.469 --> 39:09.767
You girls are all trying
to break in, right?

39:10.338 --> 39:12.203
Darling, I'm in.

39:12.574 --> 39:14.974
Congratulations.
How about Betty?

39:16.144 --> 39:17.509
Maybe once.

39:18.012 --> 39:19.639
Maybe not at all.

39:20.615 --> 39:22.139
She came around
last Christmas,

39:22.217 --> 39:24.208
bragging about
getting her big break.

39:24.652 --> 39:28.315
Guess after all
those screen tests,
she finally got a part.

39:28.390 --> 39:29.414
But,

39:29.958 --> 39:33.416
she had a tendency to...

39:33.661 --> 39:34.889
Stretch the truth?

39:34.963 --> 39:36.225
No.

39:36.431 --> 39:38.058
She fucking lied.

39:39.868 --> 39:42.234
Do you know the names
of any of her boyfriends?

39:49.077 --> 39:51.204
What is it?
You can tell me.

39:53.081 --> 39:54.139
Well,

39:54.716 --> 39:56.980
I do remember,
before she split,

39:57.051 --> 39:58.211
her and Lorna...

39:58.286 --> 39:59.446
Mertz?

40:00.021 --> 40:02.046
Yeah. Her and Lorna Mertz.

40:03.191 --> 40:06.160
I mean I don't want to
tell any tales out of school

40:06.628 --> 40:09.563
but I do remember them being
up on Hollywood Boulevard

40:09.631 --> 40:11.826
speaking to this older woman.

40:12.167 --> 40:13.361
And she,

40:13.668 --> 40:17.365
she was wearing a man's suit
and had a man's short haircut.

40:18.573 --> 40:20.598
But it was just that once.

40:23.044 --> 40:26.138
Miss Saddon,
are you saying they
were talking to a lesbian?

40:36.090 --> 40:37.580
Your driver's here.

40:37.659 --> 40:39.320
Yeah. I got to go.

