Four more days, and it's over.

47:55.062 --> 47:58.122
Dwight, you can be
so gutless sometimes,
you know that?

48:01.102 --> 48:03.036
<i>Three days</i>
<i>since we killed four men.</i>

48:03.104 --> 48:05.538
<i>Three days</i>
<i>until Bobby DeWitt got out.</i>

48:05.606 --> 48:09.508
<i>I tried to tell myself</i>
<i>I was the sturdy leg</i>
<i>in our little triangle.</i>

48:09.577 --> 48:11.067
<i>I was worried it was true.</i>

48:44.078 --> 48:46.046
Slumming, Miss Linscott?

48:48.449 --> 48:49.711
I am now.

48:50.384 --> 48:52.375
Daddy spying on me again?

48:53.854 --> 48:56.254
"Maddy, girl,
you shouldn't
be congregating

48:56.324 --> 48:58.451
"in such unsuitable places."

48:58.526 --> 49:00.118
I'm a policeman.

49:02.263 --> 49:03.890
That's a new one.

49:05.933 --> 49:07.195
Homicide.

49:07.835 --> 49:09.632
Let's try Elizabeth Short
and Lorna Mertz.

49:09.704 --> 49:11.569
I know you knew them,
so don't jerk me off.

49:11.639 --> 49:15.075
Otherwise, it's downtown
and a whole lot of publicity.

49:26.187 --> 49:27.950
This is all a fluke.

49:28.055 --> 49:30.250
I met them at LaVerne's
last fall.

49:30.324 --> 49:33.020
Betty, maybe one time.
Lorna, a couple.

49:33.127 --> 49:36.585
They'd come in
to cadge a drink
or a meal off a sister.

49:37.565 --> 49:39.863
So why'd you rabbit
last night?

49:40.001 --> 49:42.595
Mister,
my father is Emmett Linscott.

49:45.039 --> 49:46.802
The Emmett Linscott?

49:47.241 --> 49:49.607
He built half of Hollywood
and Long Beach.

49:49.677 --> 49:51.542
Imagine the headlines,

49:52.546 --> 49:56.107
"Construction Tycoon's
Daughter Questioned
in Dahlia Case.

49:56.183 --> 49:57.775
"Footsie
at Lesbian Nightclub."

49:57.852 --> 49:59.080
Get the picture?

49:59.153 --> 50:00.643
Technicolor.

50:01.622 --> 50:03.613
So what'd you talk about?

50:04.859 --> 50:05.917
When?

50:05.993 --> 50:07.688
When you were playing footsie.

50:11.866 --> 50:16.701
Lorna talked about her stupid
boyfriend back in Hicktown,
Nebraska, or wherever.

50:17.538 --> 50:20.564
Betty talked about the latest
issue of <i>Screen World</i>.

50:21.675 --> 50:25.076
Starlets, Hollywood dreams,
the whole sad nine yards.

50:25.546 --> 50:28.276
So, did Betty ever tell you
about a movie she was in?

50:28.349 --> 50:31.841
On a conversational level,
they were right up there
with you.

50:31.919 --> 50:33.944
Cute. Answer the question.

50:35.222 --> 50:38.680
Look, I'm tired.
Do you want my alibi
so I can go home?

50:39.927 --> 50:41.019
Sure.

50:41.562 --> 50:46.499
My family and I were in Laguna
from Sunday through Thursday,
along with the servants.

50:46.567 --> 50:48.228
If you want verification,
call Daddy,

50:48.302 --> 50:50.395
but please be discreet.

50:56.977 --> 50:57.966
So,

51:00.047 --> 51:02.880
what do I have to do to keep
my name out of the papers?

51:02.950 --> 51:04.577
What do you mean?

51:05.786 --> 51:07.879
That's not very convincing.

51:09.457 --> 51:12.426
I don't need
your Daddy's money,
if that's what you're saying.

51:12.493 --> 51:14.620
You know it's not
what I'm saying.

51:18.265 --> 51:19.789
I might be convinced.

51:22.002 --> 51:23.799
Tomorrow night, 8:00.

51:24.238 --> 51:27.139
My address is 482
South Muirfield,
Hancock Park.

51:27.208 --> 51:28.641
I know the address.

51:28.709 --> 51:30.108
Not surprised.

51:30.244 --> 51:31.336
Pick me up.

51:31.412 --> 51:33.903
Like a gentleman,
not like a cop.

51:34.949 --> 51:36.644
Oh, one more thing.

51:36.851 --> 51:38.011
What's your name?

51:38.085 --> 51:39.279
Bucky Bleichert.

51:39.353 --> 51:40.342
Bucky?

51:42.189 --> 51:43.781
I'll try to remember.

51:44.592 --> 51:46.583
I can hear you just fine.

51:49.697 --> 51:52.860
Look, ma'am, you mind?
I've just learned to type.

51:53.234 --> 51:56.294
Yes, I understand.
A werewolf and Red Sheridan.

51:58.139 --> 52:00.733
What if the werewolf
is Red Sheridan?

52:01.575 --> 52:04.009
Yes, that would be
more efficient.

52:06.680 --> 52:08.272
I love tip duty.

52:09.283 --> 52:10.545
How's Kay?

52:10.684 --> 52:11.946
Not good.

52:12.353 --> 52:15.982
You mind if I bunk out
at your pop's place
for a few days?

52:16.323 --> 52:17.517
Sure.

52:17.591 --> 52:19.081
Thanks.

52:27.835 --> 52:29.063
DeWitt gets out tomorrow,
Lee.

52:29.136 --> 52:30.797
I was thinking maybe
I should talk to him.

52:34.542 --> 52:36.271
Blanchard, Homicide.

52:36.510 --> 52:37.602
Lee.

53:00.067 --> 53:02.592
All right, people,
let's get back to work here.

53:02.670 --> 53:04.228
Yeah, it's an earthquake.
I heard it.

53:56.223 --> 53:58.817
Look, I didn't know
you were a boxer.

53:59.326 --> 54:02.693
Daddy's heard of you
and he insists
you stay for dinner.

54:02.763 --> 54:05.231
I told him
we met at that art exhibit
at Stanley Rose's Book Shop.

54:05.299 --> 54:08.928
So, if you have
to pump everybody
for my alibi, be subtle.

54:13.941 --> 54:15.101
Who's this?

54:15.175 --> 54:16.574
Balto.

54:16.677 --> 54:20.511
The paper is the <i>L.A. Times</i>
for August 1, 1926.

54:21.015 --> 54:22.482
Balto was bringing in
the paper

54:22.549 --> 54:25.143
when Daddy found out
he made his first million.

54:25.619 --> 54:28.417
He wanted to consecrate
the moment,

54:28.722 --> 54:30.246
so he shot him.

54:31.392 --> 54:32.791
Here we go.

54:34.828 --> 54:38.491
Mother, Father,
this is my friend, Bucky.

54:39.133 --> 54:42.227
Bucky, this is my mother,
Ramona Cathcart Linscott.

54:42.303 --> 54:43.930
Nice to meet you.

54:44.204 --> 54:46.229
My father,
Emmett Linscott.

54:46.307 --> 54:47.569
Pleasure to meet you,
sir.

54:47.641 --> 54:50.439
And my sister,
Martha McConville Linscott.

54:50.778 --> 54:51.802
Hi.

54:53.113 --> 54:57.072
Saw you fight Mondo Sanchez.
Boxed the pants off him.

54:57.251 --> 54:59.185
Another Billy Conn
you might have been.

54:59.253 --> 55:00.345
Thanks.

55:00.421 --> 55:01.752
Can I get you something?
Sure.

55:01.822 --> 55:04.222
I'll get it, Daddy.
Okay, darling.

55:04.291 --> 55:07.454
Mondo gave a good show.
Whatever happened to him?

55:08.162 --> 55:09.754
Heroin overdose.

55:09.930 --> 55:11.158
Too bad.

55:11.699 --> 55:13.496
He shamed his family.

55:14.501 --> 55:16.469
And speaking of families,

55:16.770 --> 55:18.567
Ramona, Martha.

55:19.540 --> 55:21.974
That's our best Glenlivet,
laddie.

55:26.580 --> 55:30.414
Madeleine says nice things
about you.

55:31.652 --> 55:32.812
Daddy,

55:34.421 --> 55:35.786
can we eat?

55:36.690 --> 55:39.284
Bucky and I want
to catch a 9:30 show.

55:40.427 --> 55:42.156
Of course, darling.

55:48.602 --> 55:49.762
Dig in, lad.

55:49.870 --> 55:52.202
Hearty fare breeds
hearty people.

55:52.272 --> 55:54.672
Haute cuisine breeds
degenerates.

55:55.542 --> 55:57.908
I want to draw
Mr. Bleichert, Daddy.

55:57.978 --> 56:00.640
You're in for
a cruel caricaturing, Bucky.

56:00.714 --> 56:04.241
Maddy's my pretty one,
but Martha's
my certified genius.

56:04.618 --> 56:06.848
What kind of a name
is Bleichert? Dutch?

56:06.920 --> 56:08.114
German.

56:08.889 --> 56:11.016
A great people, the Germans.

56:11.325 --> 56:13.418
Hitler was a bit excessive.

56:13.827 --> 56:15.818
But mark my words
that someday we'll regret

56:15.896 --> 56:18.888
not joining forces with him
to fight the Reds.

56:19.032 --> 56:22.695
You know,
I killed a lot of your
countrymen during the war.

56:22.770 --> 56:25.933
Mr. Bleichert, have you
met Balto in the hallway?

56:26.373 --> 56:28.102
Yes. Very realistic.

56:28.175 --> 56:30.109
An old friend
stuffed him.

56:30.177 --> 56:32.645
We were in the Scots Regiment
together. Georgie Tilden.

56:32.713 --> 56:34.271
He wanted to work
in the flickers.

56:34.348 --> 56:35.372
When did you move here?

56:35.449 --> 56:36.507
1920.

56:36.583 --> 56:40.178
Hollywood was a cow pasture
but the silent flickers
were booming.

56:40.254 --> 56:42.688
Georgie got work
as a lighting man,
me building houses.

56:42.756 --> 56:45.190
Georgie introduced me
to Mack Sennett.

56:45.259 --> 56:47.193
I helped him build
that housing project
he was putting up

56:47.261 --> 56:49.195
underneath
that god-awful sign.

56:49.329 --> 56:50.421
Hollywoodland.

56:50.497 --> 56:51.691
I used to love
the <i>Keystone Kops.</i>

56:51.765 --> 56:53.494
Me, too.

56:53.567 --> 56:56.365
Old Mack knew how
to squeeze a dollar dry.

56:57.704 --> 57:01.140
He had extras moonlighting
as laborers and vice versa.

57:01.608 --> 57:03.439
Georgie and I used to drive
them over to Hollywoodland

57:03.510 --> 57:04.909
after 12 hours
on a silent flicker.

57:04.978 --> 57:08.345
Then put in another six hours
by torchlight.

57:08.415 --> 57:11.509
He even gave us movie credits
a couple of times.

57:15.756 --> 57:16.950
Mother.

57:17.558 --> 57:19.321
Are you feeling well?

57:19.393 --> 57:22.556
Would you like to contribute
to the conversation?

57:27.234 --> 57:30.328
Did you know, Mr. Bleichert,

57:32.606 --> 57:35.336
that Ramona Boulevard
is named after me?

57:36.143 --> 57:37.405
I didn't.

57:38.445 --> 57:41.642
When Emmett married me,

57:43.083 --> 57:44.948
for my father's money,

57:46.286 --> 57:48.982
he promised my family
that he would use
his influence

57:49.056 --> 57:51.115
with the City Zoning Board

57:51.225 --> 57:53.557
to have a street named
after me.

57:55.462 --> 57:57.362
But all he could manage

57:58.599 --> 58:00.362
was a dead-end block

58:01.168 --> 58:03.068
in a red-light district

58:04.404 --> 58:06.872
in Lincoln Heights.

58:08.075 --> 58:11.511
Are you familiar with
the neighborhood,
Mr. Bleichert?

58:12.779 --> 58:14.371
I grew up there.

58:19.052 --> 58:20.314
Yes, well,

58:20.854 --> 58:24.153
then you'll know
that Mexican prostitutes

58:25.158 --> 58:27.353
expose themselves
in windows.

58:29.196 --> 58:33.155
I hear many of them
know Mr. Linscott by name.

58:33.367 --> 58:34.857
That's enough!

58:37.638 --> 58:42.473
I will sing for my supper

58:42.876 --> 58:46.073
when Mayor Bowron comes
to dinner,

58:46.146 --> 58:48.774
but not

58:48.849 --> 58:52.250
for Madeleine's male whores.

58:52.653 --> 58:54.780
He's a common policeman.

58:54.855 --> 58:56.049
My God, Emmett!

58:58.725 --> 59:00.522
How little you think of me.

59:15.709 --> 59:19.167
I'm sorry.
I'm really so sorry.

59:22.082 --> 59:23.344
Mr. Bleichert.

